# Architecture ref: ARCHITECTURE_v1.0.md §8
#
# Copy to .env and fill in, for local dev. Both values are PUBLIC by
# design -- they ship in the client bundle and RLS is the actual
# security gate.
#
# These same two values ALSO need to be added as GitHub repo secrets
# (Settings > Secrets and variables > Actions), under these exact names,
# so the deploy workflow can bake them into the production build --
# see the README's "First deploy checklist." That's a different thing
# from SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY and TMDB_API_KEY, which are also repo
# secrets but never reach the client at all.
#
# Find both under: Supabase dashboard > Project Settings > API
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=hhttps://supabase.com/dashboard/project/ibdksabroleicczuuuzk
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=sb_publishable_OByjNLxwL6EblkJg2iePHA_GM9-5ver
